  "time_ut": 1657625315,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8a\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bc8, \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc0 \u0bae\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b85\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9c\u0bae\u0bcd\u0b87\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b89\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bbe \u0b9a\u0baa\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We strongly condemn the attack on journalists and the burning of Prime Minister's house - All Sri Lanka Jamiyatul Ulama Sabha",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The All Sri Lankan Jamiatul Ulema Sabha expressed its strong condemnation of the severe assault on journalists and the burning of the Prime Minister's house.",
        "The All Sri Lankan Jamiatul Ulama has strongly condemned the burning of the Prime Minister's house during the popular uprising on 9.7.2022 in the country and has demanded that those involved be properly identified and brought to justice.",
        "It is the right of people to express their views democratically. However, we kindly request that the demonstrators should behave in accordance with the relevant laws of the country while carrying out demonstrations, without any harm to life and property and public property and without resorting to violence.",
        "Also, we strongly condemn the attack on journalists in the demonstration area and pray for the health of the injured.",
        "At this time, everyone should consider the fact that people are suffering because they are unable to fulfill even their basic needs and are without fuel, electricity, food, medicines, etc. and come forward to help the needy.",
        "The All Sri Lankan Jamiatul Ulama Sabha further said that each of us should act responsibly to build peace in our motherland and lead it through development."
      ],
